Class SearchTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • src.SearchTree
  • public class SearchTree
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides all the functionality needed to get a move to make. It contains all the information in which way the move should be calculated.

    • Constructor Detail

      • SearchTree

        public SearchTree​(Map map,
                  boolean printOn,
                  boolean ServerLog,
                  boolean extendedPrint,
                  int myPlayerNr,
                  boolean useMS,
                  boolean useBRS,
                  boolean useKH,
                  boolean useMonteCarloTreeSearch,
                  double[][] multiplier,
                  StaticHeuristicPerPhase shpp)
        This Constructor lays the Foundation off our SearchTree, where most Functions can be enabled or disabled.
        Parameters:
        map - The Current Map
        printOn - Enables Basic Prints on the Console
        ServerLog - Enables the most essential Prints on the Console
        extendedPrint - Enables the extended Prints on the Console
        myPlayerNr - The Number of our Client.
        useMS - Enables MoveSorting
        useBRS - Enables Best Reply Search
        useKH - Enables Killer Heuristic
        useMonteCarloTreeSearch - Enables MonteCarloTreeSearch
        multiplier - Sets the Evaluation Multipliers to the given ones.
        shpp - Sets the StaticHeuristic Part.

        public int[] getMove​(Map map,
                     boolean timed,
                     int depth,
                     boolean phaseOne,
                     long upperTimeLimit,
                     int moveCounter)
        This Function returns the currently best Move we can make given all the inputs.
        Parameters:
        map - The Current Map Situation
        timed - Indicates if the Move is timed or not
        depth - The Maximum Depth to search.
        phaseOne - Indicates if we are in Phase One or not
        upperTimeLimit - The Current Time Limit, where the Offset has already been included
        moveCounter - The Number off Moves we already have done.
        Returns:
        Returns the Position to set a Stone, with Possible Additional Information.
